================================================================================
PATCH 1: app/root.tsx
================================================================================
Adds Fraunces + DM Sans to the deferred font loader. The fonts are loaded
async after first paint (matching the existing Inter pattern), so cream-themed
pages get italic Fraunces headlines / DM Sans body, and navy pages keep Inter.

Both navy and cream pages will fetch all three font families in this approach
(adds ~2 fonts to the deferred load, ~30KB compressed). If you want to avoid
loading Fraunces+DM Sans on navy-only pageviews, see "Optional optimization"
at the bottom — but the simpler unified loader is recommended for v1.

LOCATION: line 320 (inside the DeferredAnalytics useEffect, in the try block)
================================================================================

----- FIND (line 320) ---------------------------------------------------------
      const fontUrl = 'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:ital,opsz,wght@0,14..32,400..700;1,14..32,400..600&display=swap';

----- REPLACE WITH ------------------------------------------------------------
      // Marketing routes use Fraunces (italic display) + DM Sans (body);
      // app routes use Inter. We load all three in one stylesheet request to
      // keep it to a single font fetch with display=swap.
      const fontUrl = 'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:ital,opsz,wght@0,14..32,400..700;1,14..32,400..600&family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,500..700;1,9..144,500..700&family=DM+Sans:wght@400..700&display=swap';

================================================================================
That's the entire root.tsx change. One line. The deferred loader, the font
swap technique, the cleanup logic — everything else stays exactly as it was.
================================================================================


OPTIONAL OPTIMIZATION (skip on first ship):
If you want to avoid loading Fraunces+DM Sans on app pageviews (savings ~25KB
gzipped), branch the font URL on the route:

  // Detect cream-themed routes by the wrapper (or check pathname)
  const isMarketingRoute = ['/', '/pricing', '/faq', '/terms', '/privacy']
    .includes(window.location.pathname);
  const fontUrl = isMarketingRoute
    ? 'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,500..700;1,9..144,500..700&family=DM+Sans:wght@400..700&display=swap'
    : 'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:ital,opsz,wght@0,14..32,400..700;1,14..32,400..600&display=swap';

But this means navigating from / → /app/upload triggers a second font load.
Generally not worth the complexity. Ship the unified loader first.
